The internet evolved from early telecommunications to the modern web:
• 1836–1876: Invention of the telegraph and telephone.
• 1969: ARPANET is commissioned with four initial nodes.
• 1974: TCP is specified, and packet switching becomes the standard mode of transfer.
• 1982: TCP/IP is established as the official protocol suite for ARPANET.
• 1989–1991: Tim Berners-Lee proposes the World Wide Web (WWW) concept.
• 1998: Google is founded, marking a new era of internet expansion.
